betterquesting:10.desc:8:
Seems like, in order to figure out the true motifs behind this war, I have to figure out what it truly is about.
Dimensional shards appear to be the end goal for both the Empire and the Horde, yet, other materials seem just as important.
From what I have seen so far, the more minerals and resources I get access to, the more powerful I become.
Meaning that, probably, the same applies to my enemies.
In that weird bank in Precasia, the bankers were talking about the Proxima system, and se were the Bees.
The planets in this system, and the walth of resources they hide, are desired by my foes. Thankfully, the Bubbell Alliance was there first!
The outer world of this binary star system, the shield onto which potential invaders will have to crash, is thankfully inhabited by allies.
The Bees of Rhenia are different than the ones in the Sol system. These ones are willing and ready to fight, and have replaced their natural naivety with cold, data-driven, strategic thinking.
